[[File:1719 - Salzburg - Stiftskirche St Peter - Flowers and grave candle.JPG|thumb|Grave candle with flowers]] A '''grave candle''', '''grave lantern''', '''death candle''' or a '''death lantern''' is a type of [[candle]] or [[lantern]], which is lit in memory of the dead or to commemorate solemn events. The form of a lantern is commonly used in [[Christianity]], whereas candles are more common in [[Judaism]] (where they are known as the [[Yahrzeit candle]]).
The tradition has been adopted by Christianity from the earlier [[paganism|pagan]] tradition.<ref name=tvp/>
The grave lanterns, known as ''znicz'', are a common tradition in [[Poland]].<ref name=tvp>http://www.tvp.pl/bialystok/aktualnosci/spoleczne/zaduszkowe-tradycje/8984919</ref>
